1 x <a href="javascript:card_browser(944)">Beyond the Height of Men</a>    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> After taking advice from some of the best players in my region I have finally constructed the most BORING fellowship known to man.Boring but very effective.This fellowship has been playtested to death against every &quot;power shadow&quot; deck thier is with only Moria showing any strength against it.(Hence the Frying Pan and Sleep Carahdras)<br>
Basically it is an aggressive fellowship designed to win against the larger minions in the actual skirimish phase(17-2 Against Nazgul) Backed up by Aragorn paying for possessions(remove 2 )and Legolas shredding the smaller toughness minions.<br>
If a minion finally does reach Frodo They usually get stealthed early or &quot;Neg threed&quot; with servant of the secret fire.I am not boasting that the deck is perfect however because of the large card count, drawing Possessions can be a factor but i included 4 hobbit stealths to give me time to stitch the fellowship together.<br>
<br>
Shadow <br>
<br>
No brainer here.Ive earned tons of respect off my effective Isengard shadow since FOTR.Although i find Urik- Hai to be horrible hand cloggers(I improved that with abandoning reason for madness)There is no minions i would rather have at site nine and thier stopping power is amazing at the earlier sites (all thanks to R&D for Keeper of Isengard)<br>
<br>
<br>
Thanks for veiwing this deck.I hope at least some people consider it to be tournament worthy .Test it for yourself and give me feedback please. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=25861"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=25861" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
